      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the pasta frolla",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the softened butter, sugar, lemon zest, and salt until smooth. Beat in the eggs one at a time. Add the flour and mix until a soft dough forms. Wrap and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook the wheat",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Drain the canned grano cotto and put it in a small saucepan with the milk, butter, and 30 g sugar. Cook over low heat, stirring, for 10 to 12 minutes until the mixture thickens and the wheat absorbs the milk. The texture should be like thick porridge. Remove from the heat and cool completely.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pass the ricotta through a sieve into a large bowl. Add the 200 g sugar and beat until smooth. Beat in the eggs and yolks one at a time. Add the orange blossom water, vanilla, cinnamon, and candied peel and stir to combine. Fold in the cooled wheat mixture. The filling will be quite liquid.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Line the tin",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Preheat the oven to 170°C conventional (150°C fan). On a floured surface, roll two-thirds of the chilled pasta frolla to 4 mm and line a 26 to 28 cm tart tin or springform tin (pastiera is traditionally a deeper dish than a standard tart tin). Press into the base and sides. The dough is fragile; patch any tears.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Fill and decorate",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pour the filling into the lined tin. Roll the remaining dough to 3 mm and cut into strips about 1.5 cm wide. Lay the strips in a lattice pattern over the filling, pressing the ends against the pastry sides. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes until the lattice is deep amber and the filling is set at the edges but still slightly wobbly in the centre. Cool completely in the tin, then leave uncovered at cool room temperature for 48 hours before serving.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
